---
description: Keep Strapi public media URLs compatible with Next image optimization
alwaysApply: true
---

# Strapi Public Media URL Contract

The frontend consumes Strapi media through Next image optimization. Strapi must emit public media URLs that match the frontend `images.remotePatterns` allowlist.

## Hard Rules

- Do not remove `url: env('PUBLIC_URL', env('STRAPI_PUBLIC_URL', ''))` from `backend/config/server.ts`.
- Do not remove the public-base URL normalization in `backend/src/utils/content.js`.
- Do not pass raw `ctx.request.origin` through to media URL generation without normalizing it against `PUBLIC_URL` or `STRAPI_PUBLIC_URL`.
- Do not change `frontend/next.config.ts` `images.remotePatterns` without checking the exact media URLs returned by Strapi.
- Do not assume Strapi sees the browser protocol when running behind Ploi/nginx. The internal request origin can be `http://...` even when the public CMS URL is `https://...`.
- Do not fix protocol mismatches by broadening image access to every remote path or host. Prefer making Strapi emit the correct public HTTPS URLs.

## Required Environment Contract

For HTTPS remote CMS deployments, set the CMS public URL in the backend runtime environment:

```sh
PUBLIC_URL=https://<public-cms-host>
```

The frontend environment should point to the same public HTTPS CMS host:

```sh
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL=https://<public-cms-host>
```

If another staging or production hostname is used, keep these two values protocol-compatible.

## Required Checks

After changing Strapi media helpers, custom content API routes, `frontend/next.config.ts`, deployment scripts, or CMS environment handling, verify:

```sh
curl -sS "$NEXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL/api/<content-endpoint>" | rg "http://<public-cms-host>"
curl -sS -o NUL -w "%{http_code}\n" "https://<public-frontend-host>/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2F<public-cms-host>%2Fuploads%2F<known-media-file>&w=3840&q=75"
```

Expected result:

- The first command returns no matches.
- The optimized image request returns `200`.

## Why

If Strapi emits `http://<public-cms-host>/uploads/...` while Next only allows `https://<public-cms-host>/uploads/**`, the page may fetch CMS JSON successfully but CMS images fail through `/_next/image` with `400`.
